      <text>PT.5.11 (Tan of double angle)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
Use the double angle formulae for \(\sin(2A)\) and \(\cos(2A)\) to obtain an expression for \(\tan(2A)\) in terms of \(\tan A\).</p>

<p>\(\tan 2A =\)[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text>\(\tan 2A\equiv \dfrac{\sin 2A}{\cos 2A}\equiv \dfrac{2\sin A\cos A}{\cos^2A-\sin^2A}\)
Dividing the numerator and denominator by \(\cos^2 A\) we obtain: 
\(
\tan 2A\equiv \dfrac{2\dfrac{\sin A}{\cos A}}{1-\dfrac{\sin^2A}{\cos^2A}}\equiv \dfrac{2\tan A}{1-\tan^2A}
\)</text>
    </generalfeedback>
